Reverse Engineer APK Using JADX + APKTool
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Decompile Android APK files using APKTool to extract resources and manifest files
Analyze Java source code from APK files using JADX
Identify common security vulnerabilities in Android applications
Automate APK analysis using Python scripts
Generate comprehensive security assessment reports
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Android application architecture
Familiarity with Java programming language
Knowledge of Linux command-line operations
Basic Python programming skills
Understanding of mobile application security concepts
